<paragraph blockId="2.[831,1437,1824,2077]" lastBlockId="4.[151,757,258,985]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="24" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis box="[831,911,1922,1945]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">Female</emphasis>
: Carapace 1.70 long, 1.30 wide, 0.75 high at PLE. Ocular area 0.75 long, 1.05 wide anteriorly and 1.05 wide posteriorly. Diameter of AME 0.35. Abdomen 2.70 long, 1.90 wide. Cheliceral length 0.50. Clypeal height 0.05. Length of leg segments: I 2.65 (0.80 + 0.50 + 0.55 + 0.45 + 0.35); II 2.45 (0.80 + 0.40 + 0.50 + 0.45 + 0.30); III 3.00 (0.90 + 0.50 + 0.55 + 0.65 + 0.40); IV 3.85 (1.15 + 0.55 + 0.85 + 0.80 + 0.50). Leg spination: I: Fm d 1-1-1; Tb pr 0-1, v 2-0; Mt v 2-2 ap. II: Fm d 1-1-1; Tb pr 0-1, v 1-0; Mt v 2-2 ap. III: Fm d 1-1-2; Tb pr and rt 0-1, v 2 ap; Mt pr 2 ap, rt 2 ap, v 2 ap. IV: Fm d 1-1-1; Tb pr and rt 1-1, v 2 ap; Mt pr and rt 1-2 ap, v 1-0-2 ap. Coloration: Carapace dark brown, almost black, shiny, covered with sparse white scales (
<figureCitation box="[305,387,546,569]" captionStart="Figs 9-12" captionStartId="3.[151,192,851,872]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,259,809]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[151,1429,254,833]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 9-12. Habitus of Heliophanus xerxesi Logunov, 2009. (9-10) Male from Ilam Province, dorsal and ventral view. (11-12) Female, dorsal and ventral view. Scale bars 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5743464" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5743464/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="24">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Sternum dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[659,743,546,569]" captionStart="Figs 9-12" captionStartId="3.[151,192,851,872]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,259,809]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[151,1429,254,833]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 9-12. Habitus of Heliophanus xerxesi Logunov, 2009. (9-10) Male from Ilam Province, dorsal and ventral view. (11-12) Female, dorsal and ventral view. Scale bars 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5743464" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5743464/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="24">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Labium and endites brown, with pale apexes. Chelicerae dark brown. Clypeus and cheeks brown, covered with short white hairs. Abdomen brown ventrally, covered with white scales; dorsum dark brown, covered with white and iridescent scales (
<figureCitation box="[461,541,706,729]" captionStart="Figs 9-12" captionStartId="3.[151,192,851,872]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,259,809]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[151,1429,254,833]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 9-12. Habitus of Heliophanus xerxesi Logunov, 2009. (9-10) Male from Ilam Province, dorsal and ventral view. (11-12) Female, dorsal and ventral view. Scale bars 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5743464" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5743464/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="24">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Book-lung covers brown. Spinnerets dark brown. Palps yellow, covered with white hairs. Palpal coxa dark brown, palpal tibia covered with brown hairs. All legs yellow. Coxa IV dark brown retrolaterally. Fm I with four stridulatory hairs. Epigyne and spermathecae as in 
<figureCitation box="[528,625,866,889]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="2.[151,192,1590,1611]" captionTargetBox="[172,1433,265,1540]" captionTargetId="figure-162@2.[151,1436,257,1564]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-8. Heliophanus xerxesi Logunov, 2009. (1-2) Male palp, ventral and retrolateral view. (3-5) Male palpal femur, prolateral (3-4) and retrolateral (5) view. (6) Epigyne, ventral view. (7) Diagrammatic course of insemination ducts. (8) Vulva, dorsal view. (1-3, 5) Specimen from Markazi Province. (4, 6-8) Specimens from Ilam Province. Scale bars 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5743462" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5743462/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="24">Figs 6-8</figureCitation>
: copulatory openings hidden under C-shaped epigynal wings (
<figureCitation box="[159,227,930,953]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="2.[151,192,1590,1611]" captionTargetBox="[172,1433,265,1540]" captionTargetId="figure-162@2.[151,1436,257,1564]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-8. Heliophanus xerxesi Logunov, 2009. (1-2) Male palp, ventral and retrolateral view. (3-5) Male palpal femur, prolateral (3-4) and retrolateral (5) view. (6) Epigyne, ventral view. (7) Diagrammatic course of insemination ducts. (8) Vulva, dorsal view. (1-3, 5) Specimen from Markazi Province. (4, 6-8) Specimens from Ilam Province. Scale bars 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5743462" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5743462/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="24">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), spermathecae small, with two short accessory glands (
<figureCitation box="[235,300,962,985]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="2.[151,192,1590,1611]" captionTargetBox="[172,1433,265,1540]" captionTargetId="figure-162@2.[151,1436,257,1564]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-8. Heliophanus xerxesi Logunov, 2009. (1-2) Male palp, ventral and retrolateral view. (3-5) Male palpal femur, prolateral (3-4) and retrolateral (5) view. (6) Epigyne, ventral view. (7) Diagrammatic course of insemination ducts. (8) Vulva, dorsal view. (1-3, 5) Specimen from Markazi Province. (4, 6-8) Specimens from Ilam Province. Scale bars 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5743462" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5743462/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="24">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
